What's she looking at?

96
00:07:17,860 --> 00:07:20,250
Why the hell was she here before?

97
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:23,090
I don't get it. She's always
in the way.

98
00:07:23,090 --> 00:07:27,300
What's she here for?
She's a nuisance.

99
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:31,900
You still haven't told her?

100
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:36,400
- No.
- Why not?

101
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:41,110
I was scared at night.

102
00:07:41,110 --> 00:07:42,810
Because...?

103
00:07:42,810 --> 00:07:44,970
The darkness takes hold of me.

104
00:07:44,970 --> 00:07:49,050
The more I try to resist,
the more I get sucked in.

105
00:07:49,050 --> 00:07:51,250
Even the sound of the clock
gets distant,

106
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:54,950
and I feel like I'm not in control
anymore.

107
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:59,210
It feels like I'm wasting away.

108
00:07:59,460 --> 00:08:05,030
Sometimes I have to keep fighting
the fear and loneliness until morning.

109
00:08:05,030 --> 00:08:07,230
You've said this many times.

110
00:08:07,230 --> 00:08:11,570
Hina called me up, telling me
she couldn't sleep.

111
00:08:11,570 --> 00:08:14,870
- So what?
- It made me think.

112
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:18,310
Maybe she was going through
the same thing.

113
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:20,010
You're using her like a mirror.

114
00:08:20,010 --> 00:08:22,880
Right. Just like a mirror.

115
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:28,150
And I tried to make her feel better
by telling her she's not alone.

116
00:08:28,150 --> 00:08:31,250
As I said that I...

117
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:33,760
You felt better yourself.

118
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:35,600
Right.

119
00:08:36,490 --> 00:08:39,800
