260
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:36,490
I made a mistake. I want you
to forgive me.

261
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:47,030
Hey. I'm free tonight...

262
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:55,300
- It's just an act.
- Even with the police?

263
00:20:55,300 --> 00:21:00,500
Yes. He's just trying
to win you over.

264
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:05,710
But look at the rain. He'll die.

265
00:21:05,710 --> 00:21:08,100
Don't think like that.

266
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:12,200
Could you do it?

267
00:21:14,050 --> 00:21:18,000
Would you go that far for me?

268
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:22,500
Of course not. Not even my
parents would.

269
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:23,500
Wait.

270
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:29,600
I can't just ignore something like this.
It's not in my nature.

271
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:31,500
He's just doing it to get to you.

272
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:35,200
I want someone to care
for me like that.

273
00:21:37,340 --> 00:21:41,610
I want him to see the true me.

274
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:50,150
- You'll be expelled.
- I know.

275
00:21:50,150 --> 00:21:53,020
It won't lead to a good life.

276
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:56,590
What is a good life anyway?

277
00:21:56,590 --> 00:21:59,960
Do you feel like you have
a good life?

278
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:06,740
He's heartless. It's all
a game to him.

279
00:22:08,140 --> 00:22:12,560
- I'll change him.
- You can't.

280
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:15,200
How do you know?

281
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:21,300
Wait!

282
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:33,860
Stop her! Stop her!

283
00:23:33,940 --> 00:23:36,930
<i>Sensei.</i>

284
00:24:54,300 --> 00:24:57,040
You you think you can
sleep now?

285
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:58,800
Yeah.

286
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:03,300
I've thought about it

287
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:09,090
and I'm not going to tell
the truth to that girl.

288
00:25:09,090 --> 00:25:14,860
Maybe I was a bit jealous of her.

289
00:25:14,860 --> 00:25:17,060
Jealous?

290
00:25:17,060 --> 00:25:21,930
In psychiatric terms,
"countertransference".

291
00:25:21,930 --> 00:25:25,600
While looking after you,
my patient,

292
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:29,970
I began to feel attracted to you.

293
00:25:29,970 --> 00:25:34,580
Attracted to me? No way.

294
00:25:34,580 --> 00:25:36,780
Those kind of things happen.

295
00:25:36,780 --> 00:25:42,080
Although, it's not real love.

296
00:25:42,820 --> 00:25:49,700
So I was trying to get her out
of the picture quickly.

297
00:25:50,830 --> 00:25:58,940
But it's not like I can come over
here every night.

298
00:25:58,940 --> 00:26:01,740
<i>Sensei.</i>

299
00:26:01,740 --> 00:26:07,240
If you need her, I won't
tell her the truth.

300
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:12,450
I'll try to keep my perspective.

301
00:26:12,450 --> 00:26:15,200
I'll tell her the truth.

302
00:26:16,220 --> 00:26:18,550
Sure, she has helped me.

303
00:26:18,550 --> 00:26:23,790
But on the other hand, she just
makes me feel worse.

304
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:28,530
It's like you said. She can't
take my place.

305
00:26:28,530 --> 00:26:31,530
She's not going to die.

306
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:38,840
I'll tell her. After that she'll probably go
back to being just another student.

307
00:26:40,780 --> 00:26:44,710
So make me a promise.
Don't abandon me!

308
00:26:44,710 --> 00:26:48,990
You're the only person who
really understands me!

309
00:26:49,620 --> 00:26:51,750
Don't be so nice to me.

310
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:53,790
<i>Sensei!</i>

311
00:26:53,790 --> 00:26:56,300
Get some rest.

312
00:27:00,230 --> 00:27:05,870
If you don't sleep then
I can't go home.

313
00:27:10,610 --> 00:27:13,580
I'd be too worried.

314
00:27:15,350 --> 00:27:17,200
Thanks.

315
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:09,270
If you want coffee, I'll make it.

316
00:28:09,270 --> 00:28:11,000
I know how.

317
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:16,770
Are you French or something?

318
00:28:16,770 --> 00:28:19,200
Sleeping in the nude like that.

319
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:20,980
Oh...

320
00:28:22,250 --> 00:28:25,680
It's good for your health.

321
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:30,050
Then you should lock the door.

322
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:35,690
I must have forgot.

323
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:44,730
What?

324
00:28:44,730 --> 00:28:48,650
My hair. I cut it.

325
00:28:50,410 --> 00:28:53,740
- Go get in the shower.
- Why?

326
00:28:53,740 --> 00:28:55,980
Why do you think? Look!

327
00:28:58,150 --> 00:29:00,720
- Look!
- What?

328
00:29:03,190 --> 00:29:05,640
See?

329
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:10,700
With a sixty percent
chance of rain!

330
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:12,500
It worked!

331
00:29:19,890 --> 00:29:22,600
Let's take a picture!

332
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:27,600
Come on! Just one!

333
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:30,580
Cheese!

334
00:29:45,800 --> 00:29:48,130
This is freaky!

335
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:53,540
Cheese!

336
00:30:12,860 --> 00:30:15,390
- You take the next one.
- Okay, here goes!

337
00:30:15,390 --> 00:30:18,660
- Go!
- Cheese!

338
00:32:09,710 --> 00:32:11,700
<i>Sensei!</i>

339
00:32:13,540 --> 00:32:18,210
- You?
- What a surprise!

340
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:21,040
It sure is.

341
00:32:25,260 --> 00:32:28,990
Which one should I get.

342
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:37,700
- This one please.
- Three hundred yen please.

343
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:42,500
This is Kazama Kiyotaka<i>-kun.</i>
He's a 3rd year university student.

344
00:32:42,500 --> 00:32:43,400
Nice to meet you.

345
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:45,300
This is my math teacher,
Koga<i>-sensei.</i>

346
00:32:45,300 --> 00:32:46,710
- Your teacher?
- Yeah.

347
00:32:47,510 --> 00:32:50,310
What are you laughing at?

348
00:32:53,250 --> 00:32:55,700
Hi there!

349
00:32:55,700 --> 00:32:57,820
We just happened to run
into each other.

350
00:32:57,820 --> 00:33:00,920
Is that what you're saying now?

351
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:04,760
You never know who's watching
in a place like this.

352
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:11,570
Koga<i>-sensei</i> decided to make
it a group thing.

353
00:33:11,570 --> 00:33:15,270
- No, I didn't.
- He didn't know what to do.

354
00:33:15,270 --> 00:33:17,190
Really?

355
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:20,780
Who knows.

356
00:33:20,780 --> 00:33:25,680
If you don't spell it out for her,
she'll get confused.

357
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:30,200
Or is she a love interest
of yours?

358
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:33,910
- Of course not.
- See.

359
00:33:33,910 --> 00:33:38,860
It's cute to give him notes
at school and stuff,

360
00:33:38,860 --> 00:33:42,200
but don't try barging into his
private life.

361
00:33:44,400 --> 00:33:47,300
I don't...

362
00:33:47,300 --> 00:33:50,000
You don't what?

363
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:55,480
I don't have any feelings
for him!

364
00:33:57,050 --> 00:34:00,200
I don't like him at all!

365
00:34:02,450 --> 00:34:05,690
How childish to run off like that.

366
00:34:05,690 --> 00:34:08,730
Doesn't that tire you?

367
00:34:08,730 --> 00:34:12,300
- Maybe.
- Let's go!

368
00:34:12,300 --> 00:34:16,030
- This way!
- Hey, stop!

369
00:34:21,970 --> 00:34:25,470
Welcome, this way please.

370
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:28,980
Here you are.

371
00:34:32,620 --> 00:34:36,880
- What are you thinking?
- Why?

372
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:41,500
- And what about him?
- What?

373
00:34:41,500 --> 00:34:45,830
Leaving your boyfriend out
there like that.

374
00:34:45,830 --> 00:34:47,900
He's not exactly my boyfriend.

375
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:52,400
I have lots of male friends
like that.

376
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:58,500
- I feel sorry for him.
- It's more fun that way.

377
00:34:58,500 --> 00:35:02,200
He'll try even harder after
he sees this.

378
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:03,910
I get it.

379
00:35:03,910 --> 00:35:06,700
- It's funny, right?
- Funny?

380
00:35:06,700 --> 00:35:13,020
The game is more fun when there
is lots of trouble along the way.

381
00:35:13,020 --> 00:35:15,960
- Game?
- Yeah. A game.

382
00:35:15,960 --> 00:35:19,000
It's like <i>Final Fantasy.</i>

383
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:21,630
You sound like someone else
I know.

384
00:35:21,630 --> 00:35:25,840
- Who's that?
- No one.

385
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:28,710
If you don't have fun,
it's your loss.

386
00:35:28,710 --> 00:35:33,780
Everyone dies at some point.

387
00:35:33,780 --> 00:35:38,550
If you don't have fun everyday
you'll regret it.

388
00:35:38,550 --> 00:35:41,150
That's called hedonism.

389
00:35:41,150 --> 00:35:46,260
It's stupid to spend all your
time worrying, isn't it?

390
00:35:46,260 --> 00:35:49,300
- You're right.
- I knew it.

391
00:35:50,330 --> 00:35:55,670
I never thought you were the type
who bothered with morals.

392
00:35:55,670 --> 00:35:59,070
You seem more like someone
who's looking for a good time.

393
00:35:59,070 --> 00:36:00,770
Am I wrong?

394
00:36:00,770 --> 00:36:06,280
Or do you actually believe
in the afterlife?

395
00:36:06,280 --> 00:36:09,900
No. I don't.

396
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:16,250
I don't believe.

397
00:36:16,250 --> 00:36:19,990
So let's have fun together.

398
00:36:19,990 --> 00:36:24,130
- Together?
- I'll take you along.

399
00:36:24,130 --> 00:36:28,400
- Where?
- To a world with no worries.

400
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:37,340
<i>- Sensei?</i>
- I'm okay.

401
00:36:37,340 --> 00:36:40,490
The ride is just making
me feel sick.

402
00:36:51,220 --> 00:36:53,300
<i>Sensei?</i>

403
00:37:19,580 --> 00:37:24,400
<i>Thank you for coming
to the park today.</i>

404
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:30,760
<i>We will soon be closing.</i>

405
00:37:42,610 --> 00:37:47,100
<i>Thank you for coming today.</i>

406
00:38:05,060 --> 00:38:07,700
She wouldn't...

407
00:38:13,540 --> 00:38:17,810
<i>I'm going to die soon, right?</i>

408
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:34,800
<i>She's not dying.</i>

409
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:46,200
What are you doing?

410
00:38:54,180 --> 00:39:00,020
It's dangerous. Please come down.
Someone help!

411
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:06,920
Stop it!

412
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:08,260
You can't do it.

413
00:39:08,260 --> 00:39:11,760
I understand what you're feeling,
but you can't!

414
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:14,900
Think of the people you'll
leave behind.

415
00:39:14,900 --> 00:39:19,200
Maybe it's impossible
to understand.

416
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:24,510
But suicide just isn't the answer.

417
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:30,710
People don't decide when
they are born.

418
00:39:30,710 --> 00:39:34,580
Death should work the same.

419
00:39:34,580 --> 00:39:37,000
That's the way life is.

420
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:40,200
You should live every day
to the fullest.

421
00:39:46,530 --> 00:39:48,800
I understand that it's scary.

422
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:53,240
I understand the fear that you deal
with every night.

423
00:39:53,240 --> 00:39:57,370
Didn't I say I was here for you?

424
00:39:57,370 --> 00:40:02,450
That I'd always be by your side?

425
00:40:02,450 --> 00:40:07,900
I'm sorry. Those weren't just words.
I promised you.

426
00:40:07,900 --> 00:40:12,700
I'll be thinking about you morning,
day, and night.

427
00:40:12,700 --> 00:40:17,860
I won't take my eyes off you.

428
00:40:17,860 --> 00:40:19,860
Really?

429
00:40:19,860 --> 00:40:23,270
Really. So...

430
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:31,240
Darn! I almost had it, too!

431
00:40:41,190 --> 00:40:43,850
I bet it hurts.

432
00:40:43,850 --> 00:40:46,520
What did you come back for?

433
00:40:46,520 --> 00:40:50,200
I already won the game.

434
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:52,230
She's out of school, right?

435
00:40:52,230 --> 00:40:56,470
It's over. Now get lost!

436
00:40:57,640 --> 00:41:04,510
She ordered the most expensive
kind of champagne.

437
00:41:04,510 --> 00:41:07,440
I acted like this...

438
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:12,200
"I've never been the most
successful host."

439
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:22,300
She's fell for it, and with all
the money she spends I'll be on top!

440
00:41:22,300 --> 00:41:25,100
And then she asked me if
I would be satisfied

441
00:41:25,100 --> 00:41:28,100
and willing to take
a respectable job.

442
00:41:28,100 --> 00:41:32,400
- How heroic of her.
<i>- He's just doing it to get to you.</i>

443
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:36,210
<i>I want someone to care
for me like that.</i>

444
00:41:36,210 --> 00:41:43,700
<i>I want him to see the true me.</i>

445
00:41:44,400 --> 00:41:46,820
Bye now!

446
00:41:46,820 --> 00:41:49,790
My girl is waiting.

447
00:41:52,090 --> 00:41:54,120
<i>It won't lead to a good life.</i>

448
00:41:54,120 --> 00:41:58,000
<i>What is a good life anyway?</i>

449
00:41:58,000 --> 00:42:00,300
<i>Do you feel like you have
a good life?</i>

450
00:42:02,500 --> 00:42:05,400
I choose "continue".

451
00:42:09,100 --> 00:42:11,800
The game's not over yet.

452
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:16,600
I'll kill you.

453
00:42:23,350 --> 00:42:25,190
Yûji! Long time no see!

454
00:42:25,190 --> 00:42:28,000
Hi! I'll be over soon.

455
00:42:29,590 --> 00:42:32,400
Sorry to keep you waiting.

456
00:42:34,470 --> 00:42:38,200
Let's make a toast!

457
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:58,620
<i>Do you feel like you have
a good life?</i>

458
00:42:58,620 --> 00:43:02,590
No, I don't.

459
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:08,100
I'll take you to the station.

460
00:43:08,100 --> 00:43:13,170
I'm fine. I told my parents I was
staying at a friend's.

461
00:43:13,170 --> 00:43:16,010
You shouldn't say that.

462
00:43:16,010 --> 00:43:23,450
I feel like I can sleep
so easily here.

463
00:43:23,450 --> 00:43:27,920
I'll wake you for the last train.

464
00:43:42,500 --> 00:43:48,400
<i>In the end I wasn't able
to tell her the truth.</i>

465
00:43:49,410 --> 00:43:51,870
<i>With her relying on me,</i>

466
00:43:51,870 --> 00:43:57,380
<i>I was able to feel better
about myself.</i>

467
00:43:59,580 --> 00:44:05,890
<i>At that point I made a vow.</i>

468
00:44:07,800 --> 00:44:13,400
<i>I would look after her every
minute of every day.</i>

469
00:44:23,640 --> 00:44:29,400
<i>That way she wouldn't
end up like me.</i>

470
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:34,600
<i>Haru no komorebi no
naka de</i>

471
00:44:34,600 --> 00:44:39,800
<i>Kimi no yasashisa ni</i>

